24/07/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic and her Slovenian counterpart, Dimitrij Rupel, held a meeting in Otocec, Slovenia, Saturday (23 July). 
The meeting focused on discussions targeting border incidents, and how they can be avoided in the future, according to a government statement in Zagreb. 
The two officials discussed the implementation of a related bilateral agreement signed last month. 
Grabar-Kitarovic and Rupel reaffirmed their countries' mutual political will for good neighbourly relations and the resolution of all open issues. 
(Hina, HRT - 23/07/05)
